1. Project Overview

Project Name: Philippines OS
Platform: Arduino / ESP32
Goal: To create a lightweight operating system for Arduino devices that runs from flash memory, includes SD card module support, and is secured with an account-bound activation system.

Key Features:

OS runs permanently on flash â†’ offline operation after activation

Trial key arduinophicore valid for 5 months

Activation tied to single Arduino account

EEPROM stores activation status, device ID, trial timestamp

Optional server services: firmware updates, OS module downloads

SD card support for optional OS modules

Target Users:

Philippine teenage makers and tech enthusiasts

Users interested in learning about microcontroller-based operating systems

2. Hardware Requirements
Component	Purpose
ESP32 / Arduino	Runs core OS firmware
SD Card	Optional OS modules or firmware storage
EEPROM	Stores activation info, trial timestamp, and product key
Wi-Fi Module	Required for first-time activation / server registration
LED / Serial	Visual feedback and status logging
3. Software Architecture
3.1 Components
Component	Function
Core OS	Runs on device flash; basic OS functions and optional SD modules
Activation Module	Handles trial key validation, server registration, and account binding
Trial System	Default key arduinophicore valid for 5 months
EEPROM Manager	Stores activation status, device ID, account ID, and trial timestamp
Backend Server	Node.js server managing product key verification and account registration
Optional Update Module	Downloads firmware updates or additional OS modules if server is online
3.2 Activation & Account Binding Flow

Step-by-step Process:

Device first boot â†’ check EEPROM for activation flag

If not activated:

Prompt user for Wi-Fi credentials

Prompt user for Arduino Account ID

Prompt user for Trial/Product Key

Device sends JSON request to Arduino Account Server:

{
  "accountID": "user123",
  "deviceID": "AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF",
  "key": "arduinophicore"
}


Server validates request:

Unused key â†’ registers device to account, returns OK

Key already used on another account â†’ returns DUPLICATE

EEPROM stores activation info â†’ device runs offline core OS

Optional: device can connect later for updates or OS modules

Diagram:

[Device Boot] 
