4. Trial Key System

Default key: arduinophicore

Trial duration: 5 months (~150 days)

Trial timestamp stored in EEPROM

Each device can only use trial key once

After trial expires â†’ device locks, requires new product key

Benefits:

Prevents key sharing

Encourages users to create an account and purchase a full product key

Enables safe educational trial

5. Backend Server (Arduino Account Server)

Technology: Node.js / Express
Database: JSON file or MongoDB

Functions:

Register a device to an Arduino account

Validate trial/product key

Prevent key duplication across accounts

Store accountID, deviceID, key, activation timestamp

Example record structure:

{
  "accountID": "user123",
  "deviceID": "AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF",
  "key": "arduinophicore",
  "activationDate": 1676505600
}


Security Features:

Device ID + account binding prevents unauthorized key sharing

EEPROM ensures activation persists even offline

Optional updates module provides server-controlled firmware or OS module updates

6. ESP32 Firmware Modules

Wi-Fi Manager â€“ connects ESP32 to user-provided network

Activation Module â€“ validates trial/product key with server

EEPROM Manager â€“ stores device activation info, trial timestamp, and account binding

Core OS â€“ runs basic functions (LED blink, serial output, optional SD card modules)

Optional Update Manager â€“ fetches OS updates or extra modules from server

7. User Instructions / Manual

Step 1: Hardware Setup

Insert SD card (optional) with philippines_os.bin

Connect ESP32/Arduino to power

Step 2: First Boot Activation

Device prompts for Wi-Fi

Enter Arduino Account ID

Enter Trial/Product Key (arduinophicore for trial)

Device connects to Arduino Account Server

Server validates key:

Key valid â†’ device activated

Key already used â†’ device locks

Step 3: Using the OS

LED and serial output indicate OS is running

Optional SD card modules can be loaded

OS runs offline after activation

Step 4: Trial Expiration

After 5 months, trial key expires

User must enter new product key for continued use

8. Security & Anti-Piracy

Account-bound activation â†’ each device tied to one Arduino account

EEPROM storage â†’ prevents easy key reuse or bypass

Server verification â†’ ensures trial/product keys arenâ€™t shared

Trial system â†’ encourages account creation and purchasing full key

9. Future Enhancements

Add graphical user interface for OS

Multi-device account support with license management

Encrypted keys and secure OTA updates

Expanded SD card OS modules

